<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO-Israeli Economic Agreement Signed in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO-Israeli Economic Agreement Signed in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Accord Allows for Stock Exchange </H4>

<F P=102> TA0205044094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 2 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0205044094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israel has permitted the Palestinian autonomy to 
establish an institution parallel to a securities exchange. 
This transpires from the Israeli-PLO economic agreement. Our 
economic affairs correspondent Menahem Friedman reports that the 
Gaza and Jericho municipalities will be able to issue bonds to 
raise capital inside the autonomy, while economic bodies will be 
able to issue stocks. 

</TEXT>

