<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel Reportedly To Release 8,400 Detainees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel Reportedly To Release 8,400 Detainees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904155494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1310 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2904155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 29 Oct (MENA)--Informed Palestinian sources 
in Cairo have said that agreement has been reached with Israel 
for the release of 8,400 Palestinian detainees held in Israeli 
prisons. In a statement to MENA, the sources said that the 
Palestinian-Israeli agreement will cover all the detainees, 
irrespective of their political affiliations. 
  The sources added that a detailed program is currently being 
prepared for the release of these detainees, and that 5,000 of 
them will be released within one month of the signing of the 
agreement for self-rule in Gaza and Jericho. They said that 
2,500 of the 5,000 will be released two days after the signing, 
2,000 at the start of the Israeli withdrawal from Gaza and 
Jericho, and 500 after the withdrawal is completed. 
  The sources explained that a program will be prepared for 
the 
release of the remaining 3,400 detainees, which will begin with 
the start of negotiations for the implementation of self-rule in 
the West Bank. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

