<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Sha'th's Return to Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Sha'th's Return to Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0105183794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1430 GMT 1 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0105183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the line from Cairo now is Sha'ul Menashe to 
update us on the Israeli-Palestinian negotiations. Good 
evening, Sha'ul. 
  [Menashe] Good evening to you. A short while ago, Dr. Nabil 
Sha'th arrived here at the site of the negotiations from Tunis 
where he held meetings and consultations. He told journalists: 
  [Begin Sha'th recording] I outlined to Fatah's Central 
Committee and the PLO's Executive Committee, as did my brother 
Abu- al-'Ala' [Ahmad Quray'] how things stand vis-a-vis the 
Gaza-Jericho accord and the economic agreement. A deep and 
exhaustive study of every aspect of these agreements was 
undertaken. We obtained Fatah's Central Committee's 
ratification of what has been agreed upon, and we received 
instructions for the next few days leading up to the signing on 
Wednesday [4 May]. [end recording] 
  [Menashe] Nabil Sha'th expects the Legal and Security 
Committees will now proceed to draft the agreement without any 
hitches. 

</TEXT>

