<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministers Invited to Signing Ceremony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministers Invited to Signing Ceremony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3004163294 Cairo ESC Television in Arabic 1600 GMT 30 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3004163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo ESC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Egypt has invited the foreign ministers of the 
states that took part in the peace conference in Madrid in 
October 1991 to attend the ceremony that will be held under 
President Mubarak's sponsorship on Wednesday [4 May] morning to 
sign the Palestinian-Israeli agreement to begin the 
implementation of the Declaration of Principles. 
  Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin will arrive in Cairo on 
Tuesday afternoon to meet with Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat, who will arrive on the same day, to discuss the two 
remaining points concerning the area of Jericho and the Allenby 
Bridge. 

</TEXT>

