<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fatah Central Committee Approves Draft Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Central Committee Approves Draft Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0105194394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1915 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0105194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 May (MENA)--The Fatah Central Committee, 
the PLO mainstream faction, has approved the draft 
Palestinian-Israeli agreement scheduled to be signed by 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin in Cairo on 4 May. 
  The approval came during a four-hour meeting which the Fatah 
Central Committee held today under 'Arafat to discuss the final 
draft of the agreement. Palestinian chief negotiator Dr. Nabil 
Sha'th last night briefed the committee on the details of the 
agreement. 
  The agreement was approved with a majority of votes of the 
18-member committee. Hani al-Hasan, Khalid al-Hasan, and 'Abbas 
Zaki were absent from the meeting. 
  For over a week the committee discussed the details of the 
draft, which consists of over 90 pages containing the details of 
the agreement which the Palestinian and Israeli negotiators have 
reached after months of talks in Cairo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

