<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fatah Names Key Council Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Names Key Council Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0105202194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2005 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0105202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 1 May (MENA) -- The Fatah Central Committee 
tonight ended its consultations on the formation of the National 
Authority Council that will run self-rule affairs in the Gaza 
strip and Jericho. 
  Al-Tayyib 'Abd-al-Rahman, Fatah Central Committee member and 
Palestinian ambassador to Jordan, said the National Authority 
Council will comprise 25 members, half of them from the occupied 
Palestinian lands and the other half from Palestinians of the 
diaspora, in addition to Yasir 'Arafat. 
  Among key members from diaspora Palestinians are Economic 
Department Chief Ahmad Quray', also known as Abu-'Ala'; Dr. 
Nabil Sha'th; and Intisar al-Wazir, also known as Umm-Jihad. 
Key representatives from residents of the occupied Palestinian 
territories are Faysal al-Husayni from the West Bank and 
Zakariya al-Agha from Gaza. The council will also include Yasir 
'Abd-Rabbuh, Samir Ghawshah, Yasir 'Amr, and Muhammad Zuhdi 
al-Nashashibi. 
  Faruq Qaddumi, head of the PLO Political Department, will 
not 
be a council member because the Political Department will remain 
outside Gaza and Jericho, most probably in Tunis. 
  Mahmud 'Abbas, also known as Abu-Mazin, expressed the desire 
not to enter Gaza and Jericho, preferring to remain abroad to 
carry out other political tasks. He also expressed the desire 
not to become a council member. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

