<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shaykh Yasin Rejects Setting Terms for Release </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shaykh Yasin Rejects Setting Terms for Release </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0205101694 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 2 May 94 p 
12 </F>

<F P=103> TA0205101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Fayiz 'Abbas] </F>
  [Text] "In principle, I support a just and lasting peace 
that will guarantee the Palestinian people their rights." This 
statement was made over the weekend by Shaykh Ahmad Yasin, the 
founder of Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement]. 
  The shaykh was speaking to his attorney, 'Abd-al-Malik 
Dahamshah, in response to Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres' 
assertion that Yasin could be released if he were to express 
support for the peace process. Yasin said he rejects any 
conditions being set for his release; however, he supports a 
just peace process. 
  Tomorrow will mark five years since the disappearance of 
soldier Ilan Sa'adon. In reaction to statements made by the 
Sa'adon family, Shaykh Yasin asserted this week that he does not 
know the whereabouts of the soldier's body. The shaykh claimed 
he only learned of the murder after the fact. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

