<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fadlallah Denies U.S. Accusations Against Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fadlallah Denies U.S. Accusations Against Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904191194 Tehran IRNA in English 1649 GMT 29 April 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, April 29, IRNA -- Lebanese prominent 
religious scholar Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah in his Friday prayer 
address today in south Lebanon attacked the hostile policy of 
the US towards the Islamic Republic of Iran. He termed the 
recent accusations levelled against Iran by US Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher as baseless and false. 
  "Yes, Iran supports freedom fighters and Muslims in Lebanon, 
Palestine and Bosnia-Herzegovina, and if those who struggle for 
freedom and for liberation of their lands are terrorist in the 
U.S. view, then Americans are also terrorits because they fought 
the British colonizers," Fadlallah argued. He said Iran does 
not support terrorism, but it has supported the liberation 
movements. Under the pretext that Iran has taken a negative 
stand towards the peace process, the U.S. has always called to 
ostracize and impose sanctions on Iran, but Iran's view is to 
create peace among the oppressed nations. 

</TEXT>

