<H3> <TI>   SLA Foils 29 Apr `Terrorist' Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SLA Foils 29 Apr `Terrorist' Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3004074894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0700 
GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3004074894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kafr Killa Voice of the South </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our military correspondent reports that the South 
Lebanese Army [SLA] centers in Kafr Rumman and al-Nabi Tahir 
were subjected to an abortive terrorist attack at 2130 last 
night. The terrorists used machine guns and rockets and had the 
support of long-range artillery. But the two centers' personnel 
succeeded in resisting the attacks with the use of tanks and 
artillery. There were no casualties among the SLA troops. The 
terrorists' losses are not yet known. 

</TEXT>

