<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Urges Restraint Between Yemeni Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Urges Restraint Between Yemeni Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3004182094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1750 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3004182094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 Apr (MENA) -- President Muhammad Husni 
Mubarak has addressed an appeal to Yemeni leaders to stop the 
fighting among the Yemeni Armed Forces. 
  In his appeal, the president warned that the persistence of 
the armed clashes will further aggravate the situation and 
inflict grave harm on fraternal Yemen's present and future. 
  President Mubarak called on the Yemeni leaders to return the 
northern and southern armed troops to their positions to stop 
the ongoing fighting that has killed and wounded hundreds in the 
past few days. 
  The president called on President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, in 
his capacity as president and higher commander of the Armed 
Forces, to intervene with his wisdom to stop the fighting in the 
northern part of the country and to organize matters in a manner 
that averts friction and provocation and preserves Yemen's unity 
and the higher interests of its sons. 
  Concluding his appeal, President Mubarak appealed to the 
Yemeni leaders to restrain themselves, engage in a rational and 
logical dialogue, and respond to efforts to preserve Yemen's 
wellbeing and the unity of its sons. 

</TEXT>

