<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rwandan Trade Minister Continues Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mubarak Asks Greater UN Role </H4>

<F P=102> NC0105062394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2030 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0105062394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 Apr (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak, in 
his capacity as OAU chairman, has asked the United Nations to 
maintain and bolster its role in Rwanda. 
  A Foreign Ministry statement said tonight that President 
Mubarak is currently holding contacts with the UN secretary 
general on the deteriorating situation in Rwanda and the role of 
the international organization in this regard. 
  The statement said contacts with OAU Secretary General Salim 
Ahmed Salim are now under way, with President Mubarak demanding 
that the central apparatus for resolving African conflicts play 
an effective role in stopping the bloody confrontation between 
the government and opposition in Rwanda. 
  President Mubarak also requested that all measures be taken 
to stop the deterioration in Rwanda. 
  The statement said summit-level contacts between the OAU 
chairman and a number of African presidents will be held as part 
of efforts to contain the deteriorating situation in Rwanda. 

</TEXT>

