<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seven `Dangerous Terrorists' Killed in Suhaj </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seven `Dangerous Terrorists' Killed in Suhaj </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC3004150194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1432 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC3004150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Suhaj, 30 Apr (MENA)--Seven dangerous terrorists 
were killed today in Tahta in Suhaj Governorate. 
  The State Security Investigations Department has received 
information that the fugitive terrorists are hiding in a desert 
area west of Tahta. When the security forces tried to storm the 
terrorists' hideout, they were fired on. The security forces 
returned fire and killed the seven terrorists. A Grenof [as 
received] gun, one automatic rifle, and three Enfield rifles 
were found in their possession. 
  The seven killed terrorists are considered to be some of the 
most dangerous fugitives. They were involved in many terrorist 
incidents in southern Upper Egypt. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

