<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Secretary Warren Christoper Arrives in Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Secretary Warren Christoper Arrives in Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Foreign Minister </H4>

<F P=102> JN3004155394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3004155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An official round of talks was held at the Foreign 
Ministry at 1500 today between the Syrian side, led by Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar', and the U.S. side, led by Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher. The talks were attended by Syria's 
Ambassador in Washington Walid al-Mu'allim, and U.S. Ambassador 
in Damascus Christopher Ross. 
  The talks focused on bilateral relations which were assessed 
in light of what had been agreed on at Geneva summit between 
Presidents Hafiz al-Asad and Bill Clinton. Talks also dealt 
with some regional and international issues. 
  Christopher arrived in Damascus at 1430 this afternoon and 
was received at Damascus International Airport by Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar' and ranking Foreign Ministry officials, 
the Syrian ambassador in Washington, and the U.S. ambassador in 
Damascus. 

</TEXT>

