<H3> <TI>   Christopher's Talks in Jerusalem, Syria Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Christopher's Talks in Jerusalem, Syria Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3004162994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 30 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3004162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Among the issues raised in the discussions U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher held in Israel was the 
option that the agreement with Syria be implemented in stages, 
spread over five to eight years. This was reported by our 
political correspondent Shlomo Raz. Jerusalem believes that if 
al-Asad is made aware of the nature of the permanent agreement 
between the two countries at an early stage, he will be willing 
to accept the stages of the interim agreement Israel is offering. 
  Yesterday, the offer raised at the time by James Baker -- 
that U.S. forces be stationed on the Golan Heights -- was also 
discussed. The parties further discussed the economic aid Israel 
would receive from the United States if an agreement is signed 
with Syria. 
  Senior political sources further told our correspondent that 
in Damascus, Christopher will discuss bilateral Syrian-U.S. 
issues such as removing Syria from the list of terror sponsoring 
countries, Syria's status in Lebanon, and its involvement in the 
international drug trade. Syria will also be asked to lift its 
boycott on the multilateral talks. 

</TEXT>

