<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF Bans Settlers From Entering Jericho As of 4 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Bans Settlers From Entering Jericho As of 4 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0105082894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 1 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0105082894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The commander of the IDF's [Israel Defense Forces] 
Central Command informed the Jordan Valley settlers that as of 
Wednesday [4 May] morning they will not be permitted to enter 
the Jericho area. If they have to travel to Jerusalem they will 
have to travel on the security road adjacent to the border, 
which will be used to bypass Jericho. This was said by David 
Elhayani, head of the Jordan Valley settlements committee, to 
our correspondent Gil Litman. He said the settlers are 
extremely concerned about what is expected to take place after 
the establishment of autonomy in Jericho. He added that the 
settlers will launch protest actions against the establishment 
of the Jericho autonomous enclave. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

