<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Road Through Jericho To Remain Open </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Road Through Jericho To Remain Open </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0105130794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 1 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0105130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Reacting to claims by Jordan Valley settlers that 
they would no longer be permitted to drive through Jericho as of 
Wednesday [4 May], an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] Central 
Command spokesman clarified that there would be no traffic 
changes in the Jericho area after the inception of autonomy. 
The spokesman clarified that the road through Jericho would 
remain open to Israeli vehicles. 
  Major General Ilan Biran, the commander of the Central 
Command, nevertheless decided to accede to the settlers' request 
and to open the road along the border near Jordan, which is 
currently being renovated. 

</TEXT>

