<H3> <TI>   Gur Says No Special Unit To Handle Settlers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gur Says No Special Unit To Handle Settlers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0205110794 Tel Aviv HATZOFE in Hebrew 2 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> TA0205110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HATZOFE </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hagay Huberman] </F>
  [Excerpt] Deputy Defense Minister Mordekhay Gur told the 
Elqana Local Council plenum yesterday that "the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement will not serve as a precedent for the future agreement 
on the rest of Judaea and Samaria." Gur asserted that "this is 
also the view held by the prime minister." 
  Gur toured Elqana yesterday and participated in a special 
local council meeting. 
  Gur added that "a long time" will pass between the 
implementation of the Gaza-Jericho agreement and an agreement on 
Palestinian self-administration throughout the rest of Judaea 
and Samaria. Once again, Gur noted that this is also the prime 
minister's position. 
  Deputy Minister Gur also categorically denied the report 
that 
a special Army unit will be established to deal with the Jewish 
settlers in Judaea, Samaria, and the Gaza Strip and described it 
as "complete nonsense." He also denied rumors of an intention 
to distribute identification tags to Jewish settlers to 
facilitate their passage through security checkpoints. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

