<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Irish Prime Minister Denies IRA-Iran Links </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Irish Prime Minister Denies IRA-Iran Links </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0105171194 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 1 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0105171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sinn Fein, the political wing of the IRA, has denied 
any links with the Islamic Republic of Iran. A Sinn Fein 
spokesman said that the British allegations are some vague 
propaganda without any basis and foundations. 
  Moreover, Irish Prime Minister Albert Reynolds said that he 
was unaware of any links between the IRA and Iran. He said that 
so far he has not seen any firm evidences and reasons to prove 
the British claim. 
  The London daily TIMES wrote that the British accusation 
against Iran is a biased political move, which have been carried 
out with America's coordination. 

</TEXT>

