<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Edib Bukvic, deputy prime minister of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, who is in Tehran at the head of a 
delegation, was received today by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
  According to a report by our correspondent, during the 
meeting the Bosnian deputy prime minister described the struggle 
of the people of Bosnia-Herzegovina against the Serbian 
aggressors as a struggle for safeguarding the Islamic 
aspirations of the whole world. Thanking the humanitarian 
support by the Iranian Government and people for the tyrannized 
people of Bosnia, he said: Iran is among the greatest friends 
and supporters of the people of Bosnia which, side by side, 
through its political and diplomatic efforts, continues that 
support in a practical way through humanitarian assistance. 
  The Bosnian deputy prime minister added: At the moment our 
nation pays the price for adhering to religious principles and 
its love of freedom. Speaking about the latest situation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, he said: The Serbian aggressors are 
preparing themselves for another attack against the free areas 
in Bosnia so that by occupying more land in that area push our 
people to areas where there are no facilities for living. 
Continuing, the Bosnian deputy prime minister pointed out: 
Through reliance on God and through the efforts of the military 
forces, our honorable people, and the all- round political 
support by freedom loving states in the world we will thwart the 
enemies in achieving their ominous objectives. 
  According to the report, President Hashemi-Rafsanjani, 
praising the brave defense of the people of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
in the face of the aggressors, said: The patience, endurance, 
jihad, and the oppression of Bosnian Muslims will be registered 
in the history of that country as an honorable example and 
juncture. [passage omitted comparing the current situation in 
Bosnia with others in history] 
  Hashemi-Rafsanjani also stressed the need for increasing 
international efforts by Islamic states in order to prevent the 
annihilation of the Bosnian nation. 

</TEXT>

