<H3> <TI>   Reportage, Commentary on Vietnamese President's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage, Commentary on Vietnamese President's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives for 3-Day Visit </H4>

<F P=102> LD3004135694 Tehran IRNA in English 1258 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 30, IRNA -- President Le Duc Anh of 
Vietnam arrived here Saturday on a three day official visit and 
was greeted at Tehran Airport by President Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
  In remarks upon his arrival, the Vietnamese president said 
that his visit to Iran was aimed at expanding and deepening 
mutual relations in political, economic and technical areas. He 
termed his visit to Tehran a "turning point" in the history of 
Tehran-Hanoi relations. The ministers of foreign affairs, 
commerce and agriculture are accompanying the Vietnamese 
president. 
  President Hashemi-Rafsanjani told reporters that Tehran and 
Hanoi share close views on international political issues. The 
Iranian president said that during the Vietnamese president's 
visit to Tehran, efforts will be made to expand scientific, 
technical and commercial cooperation between the two countries. 
He said to the Iranian people Vietnam is an attractive country 
because of its glorious independence struggles in the past. 
  The similar experiences of both countries would be effective 
in deepening and expanding Tehran-Hanoi cooperation, 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani said. 

</TEXT>

