<H4>    Meets With Velayati </H4>

<F P=102> LD0105134994 Tehran IRNA in English 1326 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0105134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 1, IRNA -- Visiting Vietnamese Foreign 
Minister Nguyen Manh Cam and his Iranian counterpart 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati here Sunday exchanged views on important issues of 
mutual interest. 
  Issues concerning politics, bilateral cooperation in 
economic, trade, cultural and technological areas were among 
topics discussed by the two foreign ministers. 
  Velayati expressed satisfaction with the trends of 
constructive cooperation between the two countries. 
  Referring to the problem of the occupied Palestine and 
Serbian crimes in Bosnia-Herzegovina, Velayati emphasized that 
the two nations should attain their legitimate rights. He 
lambasted the UK's policy of supporting the Serbs who are 
massacring the defenceless people of Bosnia. 
  Manh Cam said Iran has valuable experience and expertise in 
the field of oil technology which Vietnam is keen to share. 
  He said that regular exchange of views between Foreign 
Ministries of the two countries would bring closer the views of 
the two sides on different political issues and would pave the 
way for cooperation in international forums. 
  The two foreign ministers stressed the need for setting up 
of 
Tehran-Hanoi joint economic commission to form a regular basis 
for cooperation in various areas including joint investment. 
  Manh is part of a delegation led to Iran by Vietnamese 
President Le Duc Anh. 

</TEXT>

