<H3> <TI>   Reportage, Commentary on Vietnamese President's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage, Commentary on Vietnamese President's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Discusses Ties With Khamene'i </H4>

<F P=102> LD0205101594 Tehran IRNA in English 0918 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0205101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 2, IRNA -- Leader of the Islamic 
Revolution Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i received the visiting 
Vietnamese President Le Duc Anh here Monday and praised the 
bravery and resistence of the Vietnamese people in defending 
their dignity during the war. 
  The leader described as "highly positive" the perception of 
the Iranians of Vietnamese people and pointed to their 
resistance against the aggressor as a common point between the 
two nations and a suitable ground for the expansion of future 
relations. 
  The Vietnamese president in response called as very 
"fruitful" his talks with President Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani and 
lauded the Iranians' resistance during the eight-year imposed 
war on Iran. 
  Anh also stressed that Hanoi was interested in cementing 
cordial relations with Tehran and expanding bilateral 
cooperation in political, economic, cultural, scientific and 
technological fields. 
  President Rafsanjani and a number of high-ranking officials 
were also present in the meeting. The Vietnamese president 
arrived here last Saturday on a three-day official visit. 
  In another development, Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati 
and Vietnamese president discussed expansion of relations in all 
fields, upgrading of Tehran-Hanoi cooperation at international 
forums and other issues of mutual interest in a meeting here 
Sunday. 
  During the meeting Anh reiterated promotion of Tehran-Hanoi 
ties in all fields and said that formation of the joint 
commission had played a significant role in further cementing 
bilateral cooperation. 
  He also stressed the need for further contacts between the 
two countries as a means to pave the way for future agreements. 
  Referring to the first session of Iran-Vietnam joint 
commission which was recently held in Tehran, Velayati said it 
indicated that the two countries have gained major achievements 
in bilateral relations. 
  Pointing to regional issues including the Non-Aligned 
Movement (NAM), Velayati said that Tehran-Hanoi cooperation in 
the organization was a good example of south-south relations. 
  At the end of the meeting Anh underlined the need for 
Tehran-Hanoi further cooperation in NAM, cementing of ties 
between South-South countries and further rapprochement of the 
South-North states. 

</TEXT>

