<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministers Note U.S. Commitment To Defend Gulf </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0105171694 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1456 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0105171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait, 1 May 1994, KUNA -- The Kuwaiti Council of 
Ministers praised today the firm principled stances expressed by 
the foreign ministers of the fraternal GCC [Gulf Cooperation 
Council] member states towards support for the Kuwaiti issue. 
  In a statement after the meeting of the Council, under the 
chairmanship of the Heir Apparent and Prime Minister Shaykh Sa'd 
al- 'Abdallah, the minister of state for cabinet 
affairs,minister of planning and acting foreign minister, 'Abd 
al-'Aziz al-Dakhil, said that the Council expressed "its 
consideration for and satisfaction with the confirmation by the 
U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher" lately "of his 
country's commitment to defend the security and stability of the 
Gulf region and its understanding of the Iraqi hostile regime 
and the permanent threat it constitutes for the security and 
stability in the region. He also expressed the eagerness of the 
United States for the necessity to continue pressures on this 
regime so as it implements the resolutions of the UN Security 
Council which are related to its aggression against Kuwait". 
[passage omitted] 

