<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Musa on Preparations for Israel-PLO Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa on Preparations for Israel-PLO Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904164294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1610 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2904164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 29 Apr (MENA)-- Foreign Minister 'Amr 
Musa has stated that Egypt will invite a number of foreign 
ministers to attend the Palestinian-Israeli agreement signing 
ceremony, which is scheduled to take place next Wednesday [4 
May] morning in Cairo. He said that the foreign ministers of the 
states that participated in the Madrid Peace Conference and the 
states taking part in the negotiations will attend this 
ceremony. The ceremony will also be attended by representatives 
of the United Nations and the co-sponsors of the peace 
conference. 
  Musa said that the Syrian, Jordanian, and Lebanese tracks 
are 
receiving the same attention from Egypt. He said that Egypt has 
been working to bring the negotiations on Gaza and Jericho to a 
successful conclusion and, at the same time, to further the 
negotiations on the other tracks. 
  A meeting was held at the Foreign Ministry today, attended 
by 
experts from Egypt, the United States, Russia, Israel, and 
Palestine to discuss the preparations for the signing ceremony. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

