  [Text] Damascus, 1 May (SANA)--At 1845 today, President 
Hafiz al-Asad received U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher and his delegation. The delegation includes Dennis 
Ross, special Middle East peace process coordinator; Christopher 
Ross, U.S. ambassador in Damascus; and Martin Indyk, special 
assistant to the U.S. President. 
  The meeting was attended by Faruq al-Shar', the foreign 
minister; Muwaffaq al-'Allaf, head of the Syrian delegation to 
the peace talks; and Walid al-Mu'allim, Syria's ambassador in 
Washington. 

