<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Reveals 3-Stage Golan Withdrawal Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Reveals 3-Stage Golan Withdrawal Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2904173494 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1700 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2904173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 'Imanu'el Rosen] </F>
  [Excerpt] Today, 29 April, here at the Defense Ministry in 
Tel Aviv, Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin for the first time held a 
broad, comprehensive, and detailed discussion on the nature of 
the peace Israel is offering Syria. For the first time, Rabin 
presented the Americans with the details of the three stages of 
withdrawal on the Golan Heights. He did not go into full 
details, but the plan known as Majdal Shams First -- the plan of 
handing the Druze villages over to Syrian control as one of the 
stages of the arrangement -- was definitely mentioned. 
  Remarks of this nature have been made before in very small 
and closed forums, such as Rabin-Clinton or 
Rabin-Peres-Christopher meetings. This time, the remarks were 
made in a very broad forum, which is a message in itself. The 
Golan withdrawal is formally being taken out of the closet. 
  According to the plan Rabin presented, the withdrawal will 
be 
conducted in three stages. The Israeli settlements will be 
removed in the second stage, and the withdrawal will be 
completed in eight years, without specifying the line of 
withdrawal at this time. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

