<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Notes Security Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Notes Security Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305005894 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305005894 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Regarding ways to tackle the 
security situation in the country, Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi 
said that the government was committed to adopt a firm method, 
as the head of state, Liamine Zeroual, recently declared in this 
respect. He added that an absolute priority had been given to 
the improvement of the security situation and the protection of 
people and property. The prime minister further said that the 
relentless efforts of the security forces, the improvement of 
living conditions for the citizens, the fight against 
unemployment, the protection of the workers' purchasing power, 
and the strengthening of the local authorities together 
constitute activities aimed at guaranteeing a better security 
situation. 
  On ways to bring the security situation under control, the 
prime minister believes that for the Algerians who are concerned 
about the country's future, who respect the constitution and the 
laws of the Republic, and who work for the nation's highest 
interest, dialogue seems natural and necessary, and allowing the 
expression of various viewpoints is a democratic act and is 
evidence of civilization, as the prime minister put it. 

</TEXT>

