  [Text] In a statement published in Washington today, the 
World Bank has announced its full financial and technical 
support for the economic reforms program in Algeria. The 
statement pointed out that negotiations are still continuing 
over the intention to grant loans to Algeria of a value of $175 
million within the framework of the second phase of the program 
of loans for the structural reform of the financial sector. . 

