<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Tarifi: Sides Will Sign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Tarifi: Sides Will Sign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305110494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1025 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0305110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 May (MENA)--Palestinian and Israeli 
negotiators continue to meet for the third consecutive day in an 
attempt to finalize an agreement on the implementation of 
Palestinian self-rule in Gaza and Jericho. 
  The Legal Affairs Committee, the Security Committee, and the 
Committee on Detainees are trying to work out some of the still 
unsettled points ahead of the signing ceremony, which is 
scheduled for tomorrow morning, Wednesday. 
  Lawyer Jamil al-Tarifi, who leads the Palestinian team to 
the 
Civilian Affairs Committee, said that the Israeli side 
backtracked on several of the points previously agreed upon. He 
added that the PLO and Israel will sign the agreement 
nevertheless. 
  Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin, who are both due in Cairo today, will 
meet at 1800 at the Presidential Palace to discuss some 
unresolved issues, particularly those concerning Jericho's area 
and police presence on the Allenby Bridge. 

</TEXT>

