<H3> <TI>   Signing Ceremony Agenda, Attendees Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Signing Ceremony Agenda, Attendees Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0205140494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1310 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0205140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 May (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak will 
address a ceremony in the Conference Hall in Madinat Nasr at 
1100 [0900 GMT] on Wednesday [4 May] for the signing of the 
Palestinian-Israeli agreement. Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin will also 
address the ceremony, after which the U.S. and Russian foreign 
ministers will deliver speeches before signing of the agreement. 
  Announcing this, Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa said Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat, Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin, 
the foreign ministers of the United States, Russia, Norway, 
Spain, the Netherlands, Japan, Morocco, and Qatar, and the Omani 
and Tunisian ministers of state for foreign affairs will arrive 
in Cairo tomorrow, Tuesday. 
  Musa added that a bilateral meeting will be held tomorrow 
between Palestinian President 'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin and that meetings will be held with the foreign 
ministers who are due to arrive in Cairo. 
  The foreign minister said the agreement is a step along the 
road and not the end of the Palestinian-Israeli track. 
  Replying to a question on the U.S. efforts to advance 
negotiations on the Syrian-Israeli track, Musa said: We are 
talking about a comprehensive peace process. Egypt backs all 
serious and important steps that lead to progress on the 
Syrian-Israeli track. 

</TEXT>

