<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Qatar </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Receives Iraqi Information Ministry Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Receives Iraqi Information Ministry Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2504150594 Baghdad INA in English 1305 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2504150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Doha, Apr. 25, INA--Qatari Information Minister Dr. 
Ahmad 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Kawari received today Iraq's Information 
Under Secretary and Head of the Iraqi Delegation, Naji 
al-Hadithi. 
  During the meeting, the Qatari minister welcomed the Iraqi 
cultural delegation, saying the Arab culture is part and parcel, 
and its most prominent sources are the Iraqi culture and arts. 
  The Iraqi cultural week will certainly contribute to 
strengthening cultural ties between Iraq and Qatar, confirming 
his country's keenness to help succeed this cultural 
demonstration, Dr al-Kawari said. 
  For his part, the Iraqi official affirmed that this week was 
a message of love and solidarity from Iraq's men of letter to 
Qatar and an expression of solidarity and cooperation and good 
ties between the two sisterly countries. 
  He lauded efforts by the State of Qatar exerted to help 
succeed activities of the Iraqi cultural week. 

</TEXT>

