<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Source Accuses YSP of Hampering Unity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Source Accuses YSP of Hampering Unity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0205210294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1947 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0205210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 2 May (MENA)--An official source in Sanaa has 
accused the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] of undermining the 
passing of unitary laws, hampering the unification of state 
institutions, rejecting the integration of the armed forces into 
a single national institution, and not freeing its members from 
party hegemony and loyalty. 
  The source also accused the YSP of rejecting attempts to 
integrate the armed forces in order to achieve its own 
objective, which is to secede from the unitary state and return 
to party dictatorship over the six provinces in the south. 
  The source stressed that there is no use here for any force 
or individual that tramples on democracy and constitutional 
legitimacy. 

</TEXT>

