<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Officer in Aden Shot, Wounded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Officer in Aden Shot, Wounded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0205200894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1935 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0205200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 2 May (MENA) -- An official Interior Ministry 
source in Sanaa has stated that an officer from the Central 
Security branch in Aden was the target of an assassination 
attempt this morning. 
  The source said that Captain Salah al-Khayyat was hit by 
three bullets and taken to the hospital. He noted that the 
incident coincided with the imposition of a siege on the Central 
Security camp in Aden which cut its supply of food, power, 
communications, and transportation. 
  The source said that the security authorities in Aden are 
responsibile for capturing the perpetrators and lifting the 
siege on the camp. He denounced what had happened, describing 
it as a criminal action, and drew attention to its serious 
effects on unity, democracy, and security. 

</TEXT>

