<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denies Reported Polish Arms Deal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Denies Reported Polish Arms Deal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2604131494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 26 Apr 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM2604131494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Yemeni Foreign Ministry Denies Polish </F>
Arms Deal"] 
  [Excerpt] London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- The Yemeni Foreign 
Ministry has denied concluding "arms deals with Poland in favor 
of a party to the current crisis in Yemen." It also denied "any 
indication that the Foreign Ministry, represented by its 
minister, has any link with that." It is worth mentioning that 
this denial comes in response to an article supported by 
documents which AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT published last week. 
  The Foreign Ministry promised to publish a response 
supported 
by documents to back its position, in order to "prevent it from 
being pushed into the dispute which has been raging since the 
crisis erupted," and to ban its employees from exercising 
partisan activities during their work abroad. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

