<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Knesset Defeats Three No-Confidence Motions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Knesset Defeats Three No-Confidence Motions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0205184494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 2 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0205184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A short while ago, the Knesset defeated the three 
motions of no confidence in the government submitted by the 
opposition. A majority of 52 members of the coalition voted 
against the motions, while 41 members of the opposition voted 
for them. 
  Knesset Member [MK] 'Azran of SHAS [Torah Observing 
Sephardim] abstained. Before the vote took place, Moledet MK's 
Ze'evi and Ba'gad raised black umbrellas, pointed them at 
Foreign Minister Peres, and chanted Chamberlain, Chamberlain. 
They were removed from the plenum upon the order of the Knesset 
speaker, but were allowed to return for the vote. 

</TEXT>

