<H3> <TI>   IDF Patrol Comes Under Fire in Gaza Strip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Patrol Comes Under Fire in Gaza Strip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0205054194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0510 GMT 2 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0205054194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Nisim Qeynan] </F>
  [Text] It has just been released for publication that 
shots were fired at an IDF [Israel Defense Sources] patrol in 
the southeastern corner of the Qatif Bloc settlement of Ganey 
Tal at about 0620 this morning. Four soldiers were wounded in 
the incident. As a result of the gunfire, the patrol driver 
lost control of the vehicle, which overturned and plummeted 
about 10 meters down a sand dune. An Army helicopter evacuated 
the wounded to the hospital. Two of the men, who suffered 
moderate injuries, apparently caused by the gunfire, were 
evacuated to Soroka Hospital in Beersheba, while the other two, 
who sustained slight injuries, evidently as a result of the 
car's overturning, were moved to Barzilay Hospital in Ashqelon. 
  It has been further learned that the gunshots came from a 
two-story house on the outskirts of Khan Yunus, whose Amal 
neighborhood borders on Ganey Tal. The house has been known to 
serve as a terrorist hideout and observation post in the past. 
  The IDF and the security forces have mounted a manhunt for 
the terrorists, who fled the house. No arrests have been made. 
The number of assailants is unknown, although an initial 
debriefing indicates that the shots came from at least two 
firearms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

