<H3> <TI>   Over 3 Million Shekels To Be Invested in Golan Roads </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Over 3 Million Shekels To Be Invested in Golan Roads </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2804111194 Tel Aviv DAVAR in Hebrew 28 Apr 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> TA2804111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv DAVAR </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Arye Arad] </F>
  [Excerpt] Twice over the past two days, the government has 
issued seemingly routine announcements that create the 
impression that Israel is sending a message to Syria regarding 
the future of the Golan Heights. 
  Two days ago, the Public Works Department announced that it 
will invest 2.5 million shekels in building a new road between 
Ramat Magshimim and Nator. Yesterday, Transportation Minister 
Yisra'el Qeysar announced that he is allocating 750,000 shekels 
to solve transportation problems on the Golan. He made the 
promise in a meeting with the heads of the Golan Regional 
Council. The current sum is earmarked for works within the 
Jewish settlements, but Minister Qeysar promised that the 
government will also invest in improving existing roads and 
building new ones for the Druze on the Golan. There are 
currently 18,000 Druze and 12,000 Jewish residents on the Golan. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

