<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mirani Views F-16's Deal, Kashmir Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mirani Views F-16's Deal, Kashmir Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK3004100294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3004100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Aftab Shaban Mirani said that if 
matters relating to the F-16 deal aree not settled with the 
United States, the world market is open for Pakistan to purchase 
other planes. Talking to newsmen at Larkana, he said Pakistan 
will not accept any condition in this deal that is against its 
national interests because there are other things more important 
than F-16's. Negotiations, however, are in progress. 
  When asked about occupied Kashmir, the defense minister 
spoke 
of the heavy deployment of Indian forces there. He said, 
however, that our frontiers are well protected and we are 
capable of facing all eventualities. 
  To other question, Aftab Shabaz Mirani replied that the 
prime 
minister has openly asked the opposition to end its boycott and 
return to the National Assembly. He said the government could 
still adopt many measures to end the confrontation and bring the 
opposition back to the negotiating table. 

</TEXT>

