<H3> <TI>   Military Accord With Russia Seen as Serving Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Accord With Russia Seen as Serving Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2904131094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 29 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2904131094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Russian Sources Tell AL-SHARQ </F>
AL-AWSAT: Syrian-Russian Military Agreement Serves Peace"] 
  [Excerpts] Damascus, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Russian sources 
in Damascus told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT yesterday that the return of 
military cooperation between Syria and Russia will serve the 
issue of peace and stability in the Middle East and help to 
implement the UN and Security Council resolutions in order to 
achieve peace. 
  The Syrian and Russian sides signed a military cooperation 
agreement on the evening of the day before yesterday which 
political circles described as the first of its kind in this 
sphere since the collapse of the Soviet Union and the 
establishment of the Russian Federation. [passage omitted] 
  Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Boris Kolov [name as 
transliterated] stressed the day before yesterday that, while he 
understands the Israelis' concern over selling weapons to Syria, 
he confirms that the Syrians too are concerned over the sale of 
modern Western weapons to Israel. He added that, "if arms sale 
deals are not concluded with Syria, other states are bound to 
make offers. It is out of the question that the Russians are 
going to offer anything except the sale of defensive weapons and 
spare parts for weapons sold to Syria under previous deals." 

</TEXT>

