<H3> <TI>   Foreign Envoys Accuse Pakistan of Aiding `Terrorism' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Envoys Accuse Pakistan of Aiding `Terrorism' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0305033394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0305033394 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The delegation of ambassadors of Islamic and Latin 
American countries, which concluded its four-day visit of Jammu 
and Kashmir, blamed Islamabad for aiding and abetting terrorism 
in Kashmir valley. Reports say that the ambassadors were 
convinced that Pakistan is behind terrorism in the state. The 
group has assessed that ordinary people in the state would like 
to see the end of violence and the situation brought back to 
normal. They were unhappy that the Hurriyyat Conference leaders 
changed the venue of the meeting at the last moment and that 
envoys could not meet them. However, the delegation was 
satisfied it could meet a cross section of the people. The 
delegation regretted that Amnesty International released its 
report on human rights situation in Punjab without going there, 
although it was permitted to send a team to the state. 

</TEXT>

