<H3> <TI>   `Deep Concern' Expressed Over U.S. F-16 Sale to Pakistan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Deep Concern' Expressed Over U.S. F-16 Sale to Pakistan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0205104794 Delhi All India Radio General Overseas Service 
in English 1010 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0205104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio General Overseas Service 
in English 1010 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has made its position clear that 
India will support nonproliferation measures which are 
universal, comprehensive, nondiscriminatory, and verifiable. 
The minister of state for external affairs, R.L. Bhatia, 
informed the members in the lower house of parliament today that 
New Delhi has expressed deep concern to the U.S. Administration 
at the proposed transfer of F-16 aircraft to Pakistan. He said 
during the visit to India, the U.S. deputy secretary of state, 
Mr. Strobe Talbott, was told that the transfer of such 
sophisticated aircraft to Pakistan will necessitate that India 
reappraise its own defense capabilities and take adequate steps 
to safeguard its security. 

</TEXT>

