<F P=103> NC0205211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 May (MENA)--IMF Executive Director Mr. 
Charles Enoch and the delegation accompanying him arrived in 
Cairo this evening on a visit of several days to Egypt for talks 
with officials of the Central Bank and the Economy and 
International Cooperation Ministry. 
  The talks will deal with the stages of implementing the 
economic reform program. These talks are considered a 
continuation of the contacts between Egypt and the IMF and World 
Bank regarding the requirements for this program. 
  An Egyptian economic delegation led by Dr. Kamal al-Janzuri, 
deputy prime minister and minister of planning, recently held 
talks in Washington with World Bank officials on this issue. 
The bank officials endorsed the economic reform program Egypt 
is implementing. 

