<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Approves Budget, Investment Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Approves Budget, Investment Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2904160394 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1500 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2904160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet last night approved the draft state 
budget for the fiscal year 1994-95 in preparation for submission 
to the People's Assembly. The total budget is 70.541 billion 
pounds. The cabinet also approved the draft investment plan for 
1994-95, which is the third year of the current Five-Year Plan. 
The total investments will be about 35 billion pounds. 
  During its meeting under Prime Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi, 
which continued until late last night, the cabinet reviewed the 
results of President Husni Mubarak's visits to Oman, China, the 
United Arab Emirates, Bahrain, and Saudi Arabia. The cabinet 
adopted a number of recommendations for implementation of what 
was agreed upon between President Mubarak and the leaders of 
these states. 

</TEXT>

