<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attackers of Prime Minister Executed 3 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attackers of Prime Minister Executed 3 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305074794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0727 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0305074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 May (MENA)--Five defendants sentenced to 
death in connection with the assassination attempt on Prime 
Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi were executed today. They are: 
Al-Sayyid Salah al- Sayyid Sulayman, 'Isam Muhammad 
'Abd-al-Rahman Tuni, Nur-al-Din Sulayman Muhammad 'Ali, Amin 
Isma'il Musaylihi Salim, and Tariq 'Abd-al-Nabi Hasan al-Fahl. 
  A military court on 17 March sentenced nine defendants in 
the 
case to death, four of them in absentia. Three other defendants 
were sentenced to 15 years at hard labor, one defendant to five 
years at hard labor, one defendant (fugitive) to three years, 
and one defendant (fugitive) was acquitted. 

</TEXT>

