<H3> <TI>   Unified National Congress Reviews Opposition Position </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unified National Congress Reviews Opposition Position </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2904145094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 29 Apr 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2904145094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Expanded Opposition Conference </F>
Reviews Position on Baghdad"] 
  [Excerpt] London, Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- The Unified 
Iraqi National Congress held an expanded meeting to study the 
position on the Iraqi scene and review the position of Iraqi 
opposition organizations. Elsewhere, it has been announced in 
Baghdad that senior Iraqi officials have joined a new military 
and political organization called the "Saddamites Union" led by 
the Iraqi president's son 'Udayy. 
  The National Congress (the Iraqi opposition's main 
apparatus) 
held an expanded meeting in its headquarters in Salah al-Din, 
north Iraq, last Tuesday. A statement issued by the congress, a 
copy of which AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT has received, said that the 
meeting was attended by Mas'ud Barzani and Major General Hasan 
al-Naqib, members of the congress' presidential council, in 
addition to the chairman of the executive council and a number 
of its members and some members of the consultative 
constitutional council and the national society. The meeting 
discussed critical domestic conditions, ways of bringing about 
change, international developments affecting the Iraqi scene, 
and ways of toppling the dictatorial regime in Baghdad. 
  The congress' statement pointed out that the meeting 
condemned the regime's repressive practices, which have been 
stepped up recently in the center and the south. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

