<H3> <TI>   Foreign Diplomats Said Concerned About Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Diplomats Said Concerned About Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205121894 Tehran IRNA in English 0857 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0205121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 2, IRNA -- [Words indistinct] formed a 
"defence committee" aimed at foiling attacks by the 
Baghdad-based terrorist Mujahedeen Khalq Organization (MKO), a 
weekly disclosed here Monday. The bi-lingual weekly 'KAYHAN 
HAVA'I' in its latest issue further wrote that the committee, in 
its first reaction to MKO attacks on foreigners in Iraq, has 
requested the Iraqi government to provide more security to 
foreign diplomats based in that country. 
  "Over the past few months, foreign diplomatic missions in 
Iraq, including the Iranian Embassy, have complained about 
increasing terrorist attacks and the plunder of their property 
by the MKO," according to the weekly. 
  It referred to March 22 incident in which four shots were 
fired by MKO assailants at Djibouti's charge d'affaires in Iraq, 
stealing of an Iranian embassy vehicle a few days after the 
incident and December assassination of Caglar Yucel, the 
administrative attache of the Turkish Embassy saounding [as 
received] of a second man as examples of MKO attacks on foreign 
diplomatic missions in Iraq. 

</TEXT>

