<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tikrit, Apr.30, INA -- An explosion of a cluster 
bomb dropped by warplanes during the 30-state aggression on Iraq 
in 1991, led to the martyrdom of two youths in the central Iraqi 
province of Salahuddin. 
  The director of the province civil defence said the 
explosion 
took place last Thursday [28 April] and that the victims were 
two 16 and 17 years old brothers who were grazing their sheep in 
the area. 

