<F P=102>   LD3004210594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1930 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a banquet given in honor of the Vietnamese 
president on Saturday night, President Hashemi-Rafsanjani 
delivered a speech in which he described Vietnam as a country 
which enjoys a very good position in the minds of the Iranian 
people. He added: The period during which you defended your 
country and the acts of heroism undertaken by the Vietnamese 
people in the face of Western invaders have reached epic status 
in Iran. Your successes warmed the hearts of 
independence-seeking peoples throughout the world and you gave 
valuable historic lessons to humanity. 
  Our country's president expressed the hope that, during the 
period of reconstruction, too, the Vietnamese nation would 
continue to pursue the correct and independent path it has 
embarked on towards reforming its economic structure and that it 
would serve as a good model for the world's other countries with 
the cooperation of the Islamic Republic of Iran and through the 
exchange of experiences between the two revolutionary nations. 
  The Vietnamese president, for his part, delivered a speech 
in 
which he praised the Islamic Republic of Iran and the gains made 
by our country. 

