<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese President Concludes Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnamese President Concludes Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205153894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iran and Vietnam will practice cooperation after 
signing three memoranda of understanding in the diplomatic, 
scientific, educational, economic, commercial, and agricultural 
fields this afternoon. 
  At the end of his three-day visit to Tehran Mr. Le Duc Anh, 
the Vietnamese president, said this afternoon that he has held 
successful talks on all matters with the Iranian authorities and 
that the two countries are also to practice international and 
regional diplomatic cooperation. 
  The Vietnamese president added: By forming a joint economic 
committee, the two countries will speedily follow up the 
expansion of ties. 
  The Vietnamese president said: Vietnam utilizes Iran's good 
and successful experience in rebuilding the damage caused in the 
war against America and is grateful for the clear instructions 
of his eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i, the leader of the Islamic 
revolution, and President Hashemi-Rafsanjani on that score. 
  Thanking the revolutionary Iranian government and nation for 
their hospitality, the Vietnamese president said, referring to 
the manner of cooperation among Third World countries to 
overcome their problems: Through regional and international 
cooperation, particularly the Non-aligned Conference, we could 
help global peace and stability. 
  During the ceremony to see off the Vietnamese president, Mr. 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani said: There are no limits on cooperation 
between Iran and Vietnam. We agree on all matters. 

</TEXT>

