<F P=102>   LD0305105894 Tehran IRNA in English 1044 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 3, IRNA -- The major currencies gained 
strength against rial at money market Tuesday as compared with 
Monday's rates. The U.S. dollar, German mark and pound 
sterling, up by rls. 50, 10 and 90, were exchanged at rls. 
2,700, 1,640 and 4,040 respectively. Bahar-e Azadi gold coin, 
0.235 ounce of 22 carat gold, was sold at rls. 259,000, rls. 
3,000 more than Monday. 

</TEXT>

