<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatian Prime Minister Concludes Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatian Prime Minister Concludes Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Briefs Majlis Speaker </H4>

<F P=102> LD3004184694 Tehran IRNA in English 1755 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3004184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 30, IRNA -- If the Serbs do not abide 
by their commitments, lasting peace will not return to the 
Balkans, Croatian Premier Nikica Valentic told Majlis speaker 
'Ali Nateq-Nuri here Saturday. Valentic briefed Nateq-Nuri on 
latest developments in the aggressed Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and termed as "good" relations between 
Muslims and Croats. 
  The hojjat ol-eslam said in reply that like the Zionists, 
the 
two main characteristics of the Serbs are genocide and 
expansionism, and they will not be satisfied only with Bosnia. 
  He deplored the inability of international organizations in 
solving the Bosnian crisis and called for lifting of the United 
Nations arms embargo against the republic. 
  On relations between Iran and Croatia, Nateq-Nuri termed as 
"positive" the areas of cooperation and called for full-fledged 
expansion of bilateral ties. 
  Valentic arrived here last night. 

</TEXT>

