<H3> <TI>   YSP Official on `Attempt To Eliminate' Southern Units </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Official on `Attempt To Eliminate' Southern Units </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0305114494 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 30 Apr 94 pp 1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM0305114494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Iqbal 'Ali 'Abdallah: "Yasin Nu'man Tells </F>
AL-HAYAH: There Are Military Movements Aimed at Eliminating All 
Southern Units in the North"] 
  [Excerpts] Aden -- In the first statement by a leading 
Yemeni Socialist party [YSP] official on the serious military 
situation in some Yemeni areas, Dr. Yasin Sa'id Nu'man, chairman 
of the YSP Central Committee Secretariat, has told AL-HAYAH that 
there is an "attempt to eliminate the southern military units 
present in northern governorates, beginning with the 5th Brigade 
and the 3rd Tank Brigade in 'Imran. There are continued 
provocations aimed against the other units, especially the 
Basahib Brigade in Dhamar." [passage omitted] 
  He stressed that, "despite the continued attempts to lift 
the 
siege on the southern brigades in the north and the remaining 
units of the 3rd Brigade in 'Imran, these efforts have been 
obstructed by a rejectionist position from the other side and 
the military command belonging to the General People's Congress 
[GPC] led by Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman 
of the Presidential Council." [passage omitted] 
  He added: "We hold the GPC leadership fully responsible for 
all the dangers and seditions that may afflict the homeland as a 
result of these actions." 
  The chairman of the YSP Central Committee Secretariat urged 
"political forces and the Dialogue Committee to condemn these 
ugly actions in order to prevent a repetition of the tragedies 
on which this leadership has embarked." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

