<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 3 May (INA) -- A Yemeni Interior Ministry 
source today revealed the parties behind the criminal 
assassination attempt on the life of Hasan Muhammad Makki, the 
Yemeni first deputy prime minister, last Thursday. 
  In a statement tonight, the source said that preliminary 
investigations conducted by the competent authorities have 
proven the involvement of Shaykh Naji 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Shayif, 
who is member of the General Committee, which is the highest 
leadership at the General People's Congress [GPC], in the 
assassination attempt in which eight of his loyalists took part. 
  The source pointed out that the Yemeni authorities have 
failed to arrest Shaykh Naji al-Shayif because he and his 
loyalists fled the Yemeni capital, Sanaa, on Monday. 

</TEXT>

