<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Assassination Attempt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Assassination Attempt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0405060094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0405060094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following the sinful attempt on the life of brother 
struggler Dr. Hasan Muhammad Makki, first deputy prime minister, 
in which he was severely wounded and his chauffeur, Ahmad Saghir 
Abu-Bakr, and his companions First Lieutenant Salih 'Abdallah 
Ghayban and Lt. Ahmad Muhammad al-Ahdam were martyred, after 
having put up an heroic resistance and having hit a number of 
the assailants, the Interior Ministry officials chased the 
attackers, who fled to the home of Shaykh Naji 'Abd-al-'Aziz 
al-Shayif, who, in turn, handed over five persons to the 
ministry as the perpetrators. However, upon questioning these 
five, it emerged that the real assailants were still at Shaykh 
al-Shayif's, who, it turned out was harboring them. 
  Accordingly, the Interior Ministry issued an arrest warrant 
for Shaykh al-Shayif as the suspected instigator of the crime 
and for harboring its perpetrators. Other arrest warrants were 
issued against the perpetrators. 
  Eight suspects are now in custody. The investigation 
revealed that the shaykh is also harboring other suspects. 
Instead of heeding the orders issued by the Interior Ministry 
and turning himself in as mandated by law, he barricaded himself 
in his home, along with a large number of his friends. At dawn 
on Monday, he managed to sneak out of the capital, along with a 
number of the suspects. 
  The Interior Ministry condemns this reckless behavior, and 
holds Shaykh al-Shayif responsible for incitement to commit this 
hideous crime and for harboring its perpetrators. They have to 
present themselves to the law enforcement authorities so justice 
can take its course. The ministry will take all the security 
and legal measures required to bring the accused to justice. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
