<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   House Members Seeking `Salvation Government' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House Members Seeking `Salvation Government' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0305145694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0305145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The House of Representatives met today under its 
speaker Shaykh 'Abdallah Bin-Husayn al-Ahmar. 
  At the outset of the meeting, the people's representatives 
reviewed and approved the minutes of the previous session. 
  The people's representatives then resumed their discussions, 
deliberations, and comments on the contents of the report of the 
House of Representatives' committee which is composed of the 
defense and security committee and a number of representatives, 
concerning the incidents which took place between the 3d and the 
1st Armored Brigades in the 'Imran region. 
  The report was submitted for discussion by the 
representatives, who stressed that the House of Representatives 
should make a decision to stop the military repercussions, 
especially since these repercussions only claim the lives of the 
sons of the one homeland, leave widows, bereaved women, and 
orphans, and cause immense and grave material losses. 
  Several representatives also called on the House of 
Representatives to make a decision to stop media reactions, 
particularly the exchange of media vituperations carried on 
channels 1 and 2. 
  Some people's representatives suggested that the House of 
Representatives form a parliamentary salvation government from 
among the House of Representatives, which is elected by the 
people. This government should be entrusted with the 
implementation of the accord document in letter and spirit and 
should remain unbiased, so that the country will not be exposed 
to fragmentation and splits, and in order to safeguard Yemen, 
its achievements, unity, democracy, security, and stability. 
  In their discussion, the representatives stressed the need 
for the military commanders to respect the Islamic months during 
which fighting is forbidden [words indistinct] so that will mark 
the beginning of the road to entrenching security and stability, 
ending the military repercussions of the crisis, and bolstering 
national unity. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam Khalid Karman, minister of legal and House 
of Representatives affairs attended the meeting. 
  The House of Representatives will resume its meetings on 4 
May, God willing. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

