<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-085 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  3 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arms Depot of Golboddin-Dostam Militia Set Ablaze </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arms Depot of Golboddin-Dostam Militia Set Ablaze </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305200394 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A large arms and ammunition depot of Golboddin's 
militia in Riskhor area caught fire last night. A large 
quantity of arms and ammunition, including heavy weapons and 
various kinds of rockets, were stored in the depot to be used to 
kill our innocent people. Reports say the fire and explosions 
started in the depot at 2200 [1730 GMT] and continued until 0300 
in the night. As a result of the fire, which was accompanied by 
terrifying explosions, a large quantity of Golboddin-Dostam's 
arms and ammunition and various kinds of stored rockets have 
been destroyed. No report has been received on the cause of the 
fire or loss of life. 

</TEXT>

