<H3> <TI>   Army Deployed To Help Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Deployed To Help Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405025894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405025894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a press note issued by the Karachi 
Central District magistrate last night, one person was killed 
and 11 injured in various violent incidents in the district 
yesterday. The press note says that after four days of 
continuous violent incidents the Army has been deployed in 
Karachi Central District to assist the civil administration in 
bringing the law and order problem under control and to prevent 
the situation from deteriorating further. Workers belonging to 
Muhajir Qaumi Movement-Altaf group and miscreants disturbed the 
law and order situation in Liaqatabad, Gulbahar, Nazimabad, 
(Nazam Chowringhee), and New Karachi. Twenty persons have been 
arrested. 
  According to a press note issued by the district magistrate 
in Hyderabad last night, several miscreants tried to set ablaze 
a vehicle on Lajpat Road and another in (Faqirkappur) yesterday. 
However, the police controlled the situation in both places. 
There are no reports of any deaths or injuries and the overall 
situation in Hyderabad is under control. 

</TEXT>

