<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Urges Government-Opposition Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Urges Government-Opposition Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0405023694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0405023694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Sardar Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari has said 
that the government and the opposition have to play an important 
role by cooperating with each other to solve national problems 
and to promote democratic values. He was talking to reporters 
after presiding over a convocation of Jamia Khuddamuddin in 
Lahore this afternoon. The president stressed the need for a 
national consensus on important matters like Kashmir and nuclear 
issue. He expressed regret over the violent incidents in 
Karachi and asked people not to let the matter exceed the limit. 
He asked Muhajir Qaumi Movement leader Altaf Hussain to prevent 
his workers from being involved in violence and emphasized that 
peace is very essential to create integrity among various 
sections of the people. The president said that Karachi is a 
home of Muhajirs, Balochs, Sindhis, Pashtuns, and Punjabis. He 
urged all sections of the society to pursue the principles of 
peace, integrity, love, and brotherliness. Earlier, addressing 
the convocation function, the president asked people to seek 
guidance from the holy Koran. He regretted that the country, 
acquired in the name of Islam, is lagging behind in the 
education of science and technology. 

</TEXT>

