<F P=103> BK0405085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nepal has called for a peaceful resolution to the 
Kashmir issue. The call was made by Nepalese Law Minister 
Maheswor Prasad Singh while speaking to newsmen in Islamabad 
before his departure for Karachi this morning. He said Nepal 
wants the resolution of all issues, including Kashmir, in 
accordance with the spirit of the South Asian Association for 
Regional Cooperation. This is the reason his country is making 
efforts to politically resolve the refugee problem with Bhutan. 
He said his country wants to promote ties with Pakistan in all 
sectors, including trade. The delegation was seen off by Law, 
Justice, and Parliamentary Affairs Minister Syed Iqbal Haider. 

