<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source' on German Threat To Expel FIS Spokesman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' on German Threat To Expel FIS Spokesman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305213694 Tehran IRNA in English 2053 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305213694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Athens, May 3, IRNA -- The German Interior Ministry 
has threatend to expel the official spokesman of Algeria's 
Islamic Salvation Front (FIS) in Europe, Rabeh Kabir, from the 
country if he issues any press statements or even gives 
telephone interviews, a source close to Kabir told IRNA Tuesday. 
  Kabir was given political asylum in Germany in February by 
the asylum authorities but the Interior Ministry has challenged 
the decision and the matter is in court now. 
  "Rabeh Kabir has to renew his stay permit every week or two. 
We fear that he may be expelled from Germany," said the source 
speaking to IRNA by phone from Germany. 
  "We are the representavites of the Algerian people but we 
are 
not allowed to speak. Where is the freedom of press and 
freeedom of opinion which they proclaim in Europe?" he asked. 
The source requested anonymity. 
  German authorities had held Kabir in custody for three 
months 
last year, but he was set free after a court rejected an 
extradition request by the Algerian regime. 

</TEXT>

