<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Factions Submit Draft Bill To Disband Knesset </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Factions Submit Draft Bill To Disband Knesset </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0405075894 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0730 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0405075894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The leaders of the opposition have submitted a draft 
bill to disband the Knesset and to hold new elections. The 
argument attached to the motion states that the prime minister 
has been grossly violating specific commitments he made on the 
eve of the elections to the 13th Knesset. According to the 
opposition, a minority government, whose performance has been 
gradually deteriorating, cannot possibly stay in office and 
endanger Israel's security. Consequently, the leaders of the 
opposition argue, the 13th Knesset must disband so that the 
people may have their say in new elections and decide who 
deserves to lead it. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 0600 GMT on 4 May adds: 
"The Likud says that Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin has once again 
proven his inability to protect Israel's basic interests. The 
Likud's spokesman says that the man who until a few months ago 
promised a Palestinian tiny spot in the town of Jericho has 
given away more than 60 square km of Palestinian sovereignty in 
the Jordan Valley on a silver platter, and he is not yet done."] 

</TEXT>

