<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ja'ja' Interrogation Delayed for Health Reasons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ja'ja' Interrogation Delayed for Health Reasons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405061194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0430 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0405061194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The investigations into the bombing of the Sayyidat 
al-Najat Church and the assassination of Engineer Dany Sham'un 
are continuing. Lebanese Forces leader Dr. Samir Ja'ja' was 
interrogated by the judicial investigating judge for the third 
time yesterday in the case on the assassination of Eng. Sham'un 
and his family. 
  However, the investigating judge could not proceed with the 
interrogation due to the health and psychological condition of 
Dr. Ja'ja'. Judicial sources said that defense lawyer As'ad 
Abu-Ra'd protested against interrogating Dr. Ja'ja' in view of 
his poor health. The investigating judge agreed to postpone the 
interrogation until the health of Dr. Ja'ja' improves. 
  Meanwhile, forensic doctor Subhi Germanus examined Dr. 
Ja'ja' 
yesterday. The report confirms that the health of Dr. Ja'ja' is 
good. A copy of the report will be conveyed to the defense 
lawyer today. 

</TEXT>

